Nxd4 9. Nxd4 {Maybe White should investigate} (9. Ng5 {here.}) 9... Qxd4 10.
Nc3 a6 $1 {I wish I'd known about this move when I was young. It would have
saved a lot of aggravation that occurred regularly after} (10... Qxe5 11. Re1
Qb8 12. Nxd5 {etc.}) 11. Qe2 Ne7 12. Kh1 Nc6 13. f4 Bc5 14. a3 {The idea is to
rule out Nb4 and also take the b4 square away from the black queen.} Na5 $1 {
In the analysis to Golod-Barsov on ChessPub I give} (14... Ba7 {here which is
also pretty good though White gets some initiative. If Black can get away with
the game move then he prevents White building up even a semblance of an attack.
}) 15. Bd2 ({Instead} 15. b4 {has been played a couple of times, but the
following line of play amounts to a refutation:} Qxc3 $1 ({Better than} 15...
Ba7 16. Bb2) 16. Bd2 ({If} 16. Bb2 Qb3 17. bxc5 ({Similarly} 17. bxa5 Bb5)
17... Bb5 {and White has nothing for the pawn.}) 16... Qd4 17. bxc5 ({A better
chance was} 17. bxa5) 17... Nb3 18. Be3 Qc3 19. Rab1 d4 $1 {White was rated
2360 but he is still taken apart- a very bad advertisement for the
Milner-Barry.} 20. Bg1 Nxc5 21. Rfd1 Ba4 22. Rd2 Nxd3 23. Rxd3 Qc2 24. Qf1 Bb5
25. Rxb5 axb5 26. Bxd4 O-O 27. h3 Rfd8 28. Rc3 Qa4 {0-1 Kristensen,L-Jorgensen,
