out any immediate f4-f5 breakthrough. Now White has absolutely nothing for his
pawn: in fact the two bishops give Black a positional plus as well. White
presses forwards on the kingside but it just leads to destruction.} 19. Ne2 Qb6
20. Rc1 Rc8 21. Rxc8+ Bxc8 22. g4 Bd7 23. f5 gxf5 24. gxf5 Rg8 25. Rg3 {
Or else it is mate on g1.} Rxg3 26. hxg3 exf5 {There goes pawn number two.
Three more will vanish before White decides enough is enough.} 27. Qg5 Qg6 28.
Qh4 h6 29. Nf4 Qb6 30. Qh2 Qe3 31. e6 Qe1+ 32. Kg2 Qf2+ 33. Kh3 Qxh2+ 34. Kxh2
fxe6 35. Kh3 Bd4 36. Kh4 Bxb2 37. Kh5 Kf7 38. Kxh6 Bxa3 0-1

